// Semantic direction:
// native_module is one object file or shared library participating in the link.
// symbol_table_n maps sym_name_n to sym_address after linking.
// sym_binding: bind_global is visible across modules; bind_local is file-scoped; bind_weak can be overridden.
// relocation_n describes one fixup: at reloc_offset_n, add the resolved sym_address and reloc_addend.
// reloc_arm64_call26 patches a BL instruction with the 26-bit PC-relative offset to the callee.
// reloc_arm64_page21 patches an ADRP instruction; reloc_arm64_pageoff12 patches the ADD/LDR offset.
// got (Global Offset Table) stores resolved absolute addresses for positions-independent code.
// got_load reads the address from the GOT slot, indirecting through it for dynamic symbols.
// plt (Procedure Linkage Table) contains stubs that lazy-resolve function addresses on first call.
// plt_trampoline calls the dynamic linker the first time, then patches the GOT to point directly.
// dylib_load uses dlopen_n to load a shared library at runtime; dlsym_n resolves symbols by name.
// lazy_binding defers PLT resolution to the first call; eager_binding resolves all symbols at startup.
// nm_init_order topologically sorts modules so dependencies initialize before dependents.
// run_module_ctors calls functions listed in section_init_array in order.
// section_bss is zero-initialized at startup; section_rodata is mapped read-only.

// Primitive flow:
// link: collect object files → symbol_table merge → resolve_symbols (match undef to def)
//   apply_relocations: for each reloc: compute target → patch bytes at reloc_offset
//   reloc_arm64_call26: offset = (target - pc) >> 2 → patch low 26 bits of BL
//   reloc_arm64_page21: offset = (target_page - pc_page) >> 12 → patch ADRP
// dynamic: at load time: dylib_load → plt stubs installed → lazy resolution on first call
// module init: nm_topo_sort deps → run_module_ctors in order

// This defines native module linking: symbol tables, relocations, GOT/PLT,
// dynamic loading, and module constructor/destructor ordering.
